<plot>A look at the Church of England's position on homosexuality, and how this relates to the personal stories of two gay members of the clergy in particular. One is a male Anglican and the other is a female former Baptist; both are eager to marry their partners. This is now possible with the event of the Civil Partnership Act, and these two stories show how this recent development has forced the Church of England to reconsider its position.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?210926</url></doc>
